{
  "texts": [
    "▽ Fact 2.1.3 Let φ ∶ (I, X) → (J, Y) and ψ ∶ (J, Y) → (K, Z) be BC-maps (resp.",
    "SC-maps) then ψ ○ φ is a BC-map (resp.",
    "SC-map) with domain (I, X) and codomain (K, Z).",
    "Straightforward ◻The language of category theory needed in this study can be found in any basic book on category theory (e.g.",
    "[4], [2] or [6])."
  ]
}